reviews.text:
First time here but for what everyone in my party order I can say it is a great place to eat. All food was tasty, with its own style. Pancakes are delicious fluffy and tasty. The chicken and waffles was really good with the really nice in home syrup mix they have. And the shakes are amazing. The hibiscus mango it is a combination different and refreshing.
Really like this place. Recommend the shrimps and grits.

I was recently staying in the area and visited here twice in one week. So that suggests it is pretty good.

It certainly looks the part and feels nostalgic.
The menu is what you expect and more. Healthy and modern dishes that are pretty good.
I enjoyed their milkshakes.

The service was the part that let me down slightly.
It was quite slow and I had to chase for a few items on both visits.

Wife and I generally come here for late-night breakfast after a work week. Among the appetizer choices, we recommend looking past the cheese fries, that might sound tempting, and going for the shrimp quesadilla. We've ordered the cheese fries a couple of times before, but neither the wife nor I are fans of the type of fries served, which are thin, short, and its typically cold when served. The burger is decent with a nice sized patty, but the bun felt too dry/stale; we did ask for medium, but it came out well done. The pancakes are very nice, eggs are good, but the sausage was not as great. Staff are friendly, courteous, and professional with every experience, but we do consistently have to hunt them down for refills of the water, napkins, condiments, to-go boxes, and checks :) Staff are always very nice about it though. The only area of discomfort I have is the tipping...it's a little much to have 20%, 22%, and 25% as the easy choice options...understandable, but I also don't agree with servers pressing 22% by default on the device before stepping away to let us sign, especially with the price of menu items. Overall, a good place for late night hangouts with friends.

The Silver Diner has taken the reigns and redefined the former rules and beliefs surrounding “Diner Culture.” While Breakfast Staples like the Lumberjack and Worlds greatest Milkshakes continue to grace the Menu, there are obvious healthful and wholesome options also emerging, not to mention an ample selection of tasty Vegan entrees!

I enjoyed a  casual dinner with friends and we were thrilled to discover we could also make it a Happy Hour (or a Happy Dinner?) but ordering a glass of bubbles and an Old Bay Bloody Mary! I didn’t realize the Diner also has a full liquor license!? Next time it’s going to be one of their delicious milkshakes with Vodka in it! Undoubtedly!  :)

Made last minute plans and decided to come to Silver Diner. Food was great but our server was even better! Emmanuel was great, courteous, and professional even though it was a Friday night and very busy, he came to check on us multiple times and our drinks were never empty!
Food arrived quickly and was delicious.

My family and I have been visiting Joe's noodle house for over a decade. The food has remained consistent and amazing. We always order the fish filet in special hot pot sauce, scallion pancakes. Occasionally we will order the spicy thai wings, and sweet steamed buns. The people that operate the restaurant have always been kind and they keep their menu up to date.

The Drunk Noodles with chicken wow, what flavor , it taste amazing but it could've used a little bit more chicken. On another note, the chicken fried rice had alot of chicken but not so much in flavor.

Definitely really good noodles , skip the rice next time.

So much salt. I don't know if we got a cook who was just heavy handed with the salt but couldn't even finish our meal. You have to order your food at the counter and it comes out quick...a little too quick. We ordered the beef noodle soup and mooshu pork and it was out in less than 5 minutes. That's not necessarily a bad thing but it was just so oversalted that it just made us question how much of it was precooked and reseasoned.

Mediocre Chinese food. Horrible service! They make you pay before getting your food and don’t care afterwards if you enjoy it or not. I accidentally ordered a dish that was TOO spicy for consumption and asked if we could either get our money back or exchange it for a different dish. The answer received was “no” and they did not bother with any further actions to satisfy our needs. Left feeling robbed of our hard earned money, a tasty meal, and an enjoyable dining experience. There are many other Chinese restaurants in Rockville. Stay away from this establishment!
Uff - the Dan Dan noodles consisted of over cooked - no doubt boxed - spaghetti and a great spiced sauce … but the noodles were so flabby and awful it was inedible…

Very clean place with really good quality meats. Their meats taste amazing and fresh. The owner is great and helpful and can help you buy best products. Overall if you are looking for a good quality and fresh stuff this is your go to place for sure! It is just a little pricy (for some products even more expensive than wholefood) which is why I gave it 4 and not 5.

Best meat shop in the DMV area. The quality of the meat is great and they are happy to cut it according to your liking. The staff and owner are very dedicated and make sure that every customer gets the best meat. I love the Halal Turkey they sell during thanksgiving holidays. It comes in different sizes and is so moist and delicious after baking.

I went into this store for goat meat. The gentleman who got my order was quite pleasant. Unfortunately the older gentleman behind the counter assumed that I was paying with food stamps - which I was not.  Then he said that my payment declined which was surprising since I had now than enough funds to cover payment.  Then I thought well since he assumed that the card was food stamps of course would decline. Though things like this and worse happen to Black people every day.  I just want to warn others so they know what type of establishment this is.
They will never see another dollar of my money.

Fantastic customer service.  I  have special needs due to recovery from oral cancer and Reza has picked out and properly sliced the meat to my requirements!!

Very high quality meats combined with excellent customer service!!!

Wonderful experience 👍👍👍👍👍👍👍👍👍👍👍👍
Best butcher meat in the DMV!!! Have been coming here for over 10 years. Friendly service and superior quality meat.

It was a busy Sunday evening. We were greeted and sat down at the booth. The complementary chips and salsa was a good start. The Signature Whiskey Glazed Sampler was very tasteful - crispy shrimp were fresh, sesame chicken were delicious, and the ribs are juicy. Onion soup might need more cheese. House salad was healthy. Kids meals did not have any vegetables, so just pasta and mashed potatoes.

Great TGI location! Delicious food and great service!

Pros:
Yummy burgers
Tasty fries
Fast service
Friendly employees
Everything Clean
Plenty of tables
Plenty of parking
Free parking

No stupid masks
No stupid vaccine passports

Just great food, great service and good times!

Look, I don't mind waiting...but holy Christmas.  40 min for a drink! I had to pick food up for lunch. Our orders sat in the pick up bins, drinks not put in cups yet. Had a hostess, waiter, cook,  and manager all stare at the order stapled to the bag. They looked at me, each one asking me the same question,  then just leave. I used to love coming here during my college years. Great atmosphere. What happened? Maybe I should come in inebriated so I won't care so much either.

I came here to try the $5 for 10 wings Monday's, I was disappointed, the chicken was overcooked and super chewy, the garlic parmasean sauce was pretty tasty.

I've always loved the burgers here since they are seasoned. The macaroni and cheese is pretty good too along with the fries!

I was double charge and manager Luis was rude!!! I expect my money back,,the bill was $230.46, we gave $220 cash and ask to put the rest on my card, waitress charge an extra $110.46 on my card; Luis came back and told us it takes 8 days to get it back and didn’t gives us a refund receipt and didn’t apologize.

This is one of few Matchbox locations that has brunch. I wanted to try it out based on the list of food and price seemed like a good deal...WRONG...food is under heated lamps basically dried out...had to request someone from the manager to return to the omelet station to cook omelets...I have enclosed a picture with no one present. The guy cooking omelets was on his cell phone...none of the food was covered and the worker's don't wear masks. The omelet guy didn't have enough common knowledge to cut the ingredients I gave him up into the omelet and he added salt...WHY I DON'T KNOW...THE FOOD ISN'T WORTH THE BIT OF MONEY THEY CHARGE...IF YOU MUST GO..GO FOR LUNCH OR DINNER...DON'T EVER GO FOR BRUNCH...I WOULD HAVE DONE BETTER AT MCDONALD'S..THE LOW AMOUNT OF CUSTOMERS WAS THE FIRST HINT..SOMETHING ISN'T RIGHT! YEP THE FOOD!
A GOOD BRUNCH SELLS ITSELF...Ask Dee Fair Common Sense 101/you tube

Well, I am satisfied from the quality of the food and the nice and respectful attitude of the staff. But I have to say that the menu is very pricey and compared to the quality and portion size of the food I have to say that's not worth it. Also, the waiter kept checking on us every 5 minutes until the restaurant got busy then we didn't see him for 40min. And also we have to wait for our desert for another 40 minutes. Well all together I liked my experience here and I loved the interior design of the restaurant which was to somehow different but I would say I will not come back due to high prices.
Always a solid go to place to eat. Great cocktails, pizza, and environment. Staff is always pleasant. Special shout out to Geo for great service. Save room for dessert.

Great place for bite to eat.  Plenty of room for large groups and a nice variety on the menu.  Pizza 🍕 is a specialty, highly recommend.  It's a nice place.  Check out the menu before you go, call ahead for reservations during busy hours.  Of you have a large group, definitely make a reservation.  Plenty of parking and easy to find.  Enjoy!

I l❤️ved it!!! Went after work to catch a drink or two..ended up getting bottomless mimosas instead! I also ordered the Lobster Roll and the Dynamite Shrimp, which were unbelievable! The roll the lobster was on was fluffy and buttery, while the lobster meat itself was juicy, succulent and sweet—and they weren't stingy with it. The Dynamite Shrimp was juicy and flavorful in delectable spices, while the tempura batter was crunchy, light and flaky. As for the mimosas I had a choice between pineapple or orange juices and I ordered a mix of the two.
WILL BE BACK!!!
They have a nice variety of vegan options. I love that you can customize your own bowl. I have tried almost everything off of their menu, and you can't go wrong.

Cute lil spot inside of MOM’s market. I’m not much of a health conscious eater or one that cares for meat substitutes but my girlfriend loves this place so I thought I’d give it a shot. The cauliflower tacos were amazing (got them with salsa verde and vegan crema).

They also make their own juices that are pretty good. I’d like to see their menu expand!

Always a great vegan meal!!
Located inside MOMs Organic Market this place is fantastic.  The servers are very accommodating and friendly.
Easy to see the market from Randolph Road and has lots of parking.
The food is SSSOOO FRESH and delicious. I got the  Crowder bowl and asked not to have it steamed, dressing on the side.
I also got 2 juices, The Pink Lady, kombucha on the side and another with carrots, apples and ginger. SO FRESH and HEALTHY!!
Love that I can pick up a few groceries along with a great lunch.
Would have given it a 5 star but it is organic pricey. The small juice is $6.50 each and the bowl is $9.50. I asked for a few additonal things which cost $.75 extra per item. I will say the portions are big, my 5 year old and I shared the bowl.
HIGHLY RECOMMEND for foodies!! Especially vegan foodies.

Eat here about once a week. The meals are typically good however their brown rice never seems to be cooked correctly and unfortunately can ruin a meal. I’ve gotten it multiples time where it’s hard as a rock and feels like it going to crack my tooth. I’m not sure if it’s because it’s sitting all day but really hope they can get that sorted out because it’s ruined more than a few of the meals I’ve gotten from here.

Always great fresh vegetable meals. I haven't tried all of them but have been getting the cauliflower chickpea tacos recently. I'll buy a can of wild salmon and add it to it with a little extra kick from some of the sauces.

This place is lovely! I hadn’t heard of it but my husband and I recently returned from France and were looking for some local French spots. He found this and we went for brunch last Sunday. I’m glad we made a reservation because it was packed! They were very busy so service was a little slower than what I assume it typically is, but it didn’t detract from the experience and everyone we encountered was very nice and eager to help. It’s also in an unassuming shopping center and was unexpectedly cute instead! Cute booths and bar area. They also have an outdoor patio in the parking lot but I preferred indoors.

Our food was delicious—the waffles were so light and airy! I also loved that they provided refills in cute little pitchers; it was very cute. They serve the French onion soup with a Swiss stuffed waffle which was really good (the soup itself was a bit salty for me). I do wish they did brunch drink specials (a mimosa is $11 for one or $35 for bottomless) but otherwise everything was wonderful.

They only have two individual bathrooms and the women’s room bathroom toilet seemed to have some plumbing issues which I hope was a one time thing which has since been fixed.

We plan to go back for brunch soon with friends and would definitely recommend this place to others!

Came here for lunch Sunday.  Food was okay but the service was not great—it took a while before our food came out, and the entrees came out way before the soup and salad.  Then they forgot one dish, and throughout the meal, our server kept saying she would “check on our dishes” and disappear.

I would recommend the Steak Pomme Frites—it was well marinated. The Mosiac Omelette was good too.

Great brunch experience. The restaurant has a very warm decor. The waiters are dressed casually but have on bow ties. The service was great. My friend and I enjoyed catching up and eating a few courses without feeling rushed and getting delicious mamosa refills right on time.
The waffles are amazing. The crepes, binnets, great. Warm almond bread pudding is so good!

Very good food and great service. You have to try the waffle sandwiches. I got the Panko fried chicken and the waffle was too big. But the other waffle sandwiches on the table were easier to eat. I still enjoyed my sandwich
Food was delicious. We went at an off time, and during change of shifts, so service was a tad bit slow, but everyone was very friendly. Nice atmosphere.
Great brews rotates very frequently. Deli sandwiches are amazing! We met a great group of people and hung out for a while!
Best sandwich I have had in a long time. I would put it on par with Publix. (if you know what I mean then you gotta just go).

This place is great! Since I'm new to craft beersI asked for assistance. They were more than willing  and I really the recommendation (furious george). I decided to order sandwiches. I had been staring at the special on the board, found it intriguing,  and decided to order it, Tim's deli sandwich. Best decision I could've made. This sandwich is AMAZING!! I felt like there was a party in my mouth and I didn't want it to end!! Do yourself a favor and try it. You won't regret it...I GUARANTEE!!

The Chief sandwich was so good that I would cross state lines for it they also have some great ANXO cider with is outside of this world. All that is presented with an outstanding service. Thank you so much y’all!

The best Tuna Salad i ever had. Also the staffs are very nice.  Cannot believe i have been avoiding this place for so long.  Also for the wine and beer selections are unbelievable for real. I highly recommend this place any day.

Update your hours online. If your store hours say you are open until 8, that means you should be open until 8. Not closed before 7pm. Also of you are closed. Turn off the window sign saying that you are open.

I just went through a horrible experience at this Subway. The lady was the rudest I have ever encountered anyone treating a customer. I believe she was already in the bad mood  and she started to get  real mad when I asked her to give me the fresh lettuce  . She wouldn't listen properly to what I was requesting and was  just literally throwing stuff in my sandwich  . In the end I asked her to add pepper and she added salt as well. Instead of apologizing , she turned it around and blamed me that I was not clear on what I was asking. After that she refused to give me my sandwich. When I asked her for the manager she completely ignored me. I called Subway customer service and they asked me to file the official complain online which I plan to do. I tried knocking on the employee door and ring the bell to get attention of other employees and or manager so that I could complain about her behavior, instead she threatened to call the Cops on me . She latter claimed that she was the owner and  the manager of the store.  What a nightmare!.  I have been going to this place for over 5 years and it use to be a very friendly especially an older lady who use to be there all the time.  Recently I think,  they have hired new employees who are absolutely rude. I have experienced this similar  behavior multiple times in recent past but today was absolutely horrible.

Would not accept a valid coupon. Would not let me get 1/2 each of two kinds of cheese on the sub. Basically unfriendly. My opinion this store will close soon. Went about dinner time, no other customers. Received sub that was mostly bread.

subs had a good taste but the portions and what they put in the subs are less than other subways i have been to in the area.  paying 14  with a total bill close to 17.50 is not what would have expected.  let staff know will not be back to this subway shop. they showed no concern. 14 is also a bit much for a foot long

Wow that lady that was in today was so incredibly rude. I understand if you have had a bad day but if you a customer thats there and is not being rude to you why be so rude to them. This lady was such in a bad mood she was throwing veggies everywhere she didn't wait to the toaster to stop, she took the subs out before the time. They way she was talking to me seemed like she didn't want to be there. When I got home all the veggies were out of the sub!
Another subway,  the staff here is nice . And this one is you don't need to wait to much.

Typical subway, but their hours suck. They're one of only two places to eat on this side of twinbrook metro but they're closed before I get home from work and closed on Saturday and Sundays. Annoying. Useless unless you work over here. No wonder Green Bamboo is always packed. Dock
The lady who works there didn't  know how to make a wrap and she can barely speak English. Food did not look fresh @ all.... We did not like this location.
Yummy thank you!
Hours online show it’s open on the weekend, but it’s not. Drove to get a sandwich but was disappointed.

This place has to be the best Greek restaurant in MoCo. I love their octopus dish and lamb chops. I also love their saganaki (grill cheese) and variety of dips. They also have covered outdoor seating and plenty of tables inside.

The food here is absolutely delicious. Mouthwatering fresh baked bread comes with the meal with a yummy olive oil sauce. The one thing that off put me was the odd taste of the olive oil that was put on various foods and wasn't listed as so. The filet mignon and lamb chop were cooked perfectly! The chicken was a bit tough. This place has the best salmon I have ever had. I also had the swordfish which was good, I didn't know there was going to be a sauce on it because it was not in the description, luckily I was okay with the sauce, but it should be mentioned that it has a mushroom sauce, which is the only thing that gave it flavor. If this place had better descriptions of their food I would give it 5 stars.

Mykonos is a quaint Greek restaurant hidden behind congressional plaza in Rockville Maryland. The restaurant speaks Greece from the moment you walk in. The waiters are professional, at-tentative and well versed in Greek food; they know the menu well. The ambiance is wonderful, elegant, comfortable and only lacks a view to the Mediterranean Sea. I started with a marinated eggplant topped with tomatoes, onions, raisins & pine nuts. It was delightful! A perfect start!! I ordered a mixed grill of bifteki, lamb chop, chicken skewer with vegetables & potatoes. It was very well seasoned. The mixed grill proportion is conservative so be sure to order an appetizer. I was too full to order dessert but they offered a nice range of Greek sweets. If the owner is there, you’ll get a kick out of watching him walk around the restaurant. Greek pride to the max! He’ll likely be wearing blue and be quick to share all about the glory of Greece…

Boasting success that spans more than 15 years, Mykonos Grill is MoCo’s flagship Greek Venue. Not to mention it’s ranking as too 5 Greek Restaurants in the DMV, and hailed by WTOP as one of the Top 10 International Restaurants in 2021!

Food is consistently delicious. Homestyle plating that is less concerned with Social Media presence and more about consumer contentedness. This establishment thrives on word of mouth and review-proof Entrees. Do yourself a favor and try the Keftedes- they’re easily the BEST in the DMV! Branzino and Octopus are always fresh! Notable selection of Greek wines!

Lastly, don’t end a meal without a slice of the Orange Cake for dessert! Even Yiayia would endorse this one! :)

Mykonos Grill is a fantastic neighborhood spot. The ambiance is fantastic and wonderfully mirrors the Mediterranean island of its namesake. The staff is courteous, and efficient. The food is fantastic and the menu extensive (including various Greek classics). We have been on multiple occasions, and it’s our preferred spot for life celebrations. Highly recommend the lamb (picture), the Saganaki, the Spanakopita, and the combo platter.

I just love their sauces, signature waffle fries and popcorn chicken nuggets! It doesn't get more simple and delicious than that. Also, I've never had a bad meal no matter the franchise visited. Moderately priced for the flavor and service. Kid friendly and approved family favorite!

I always find it interesting that there service and food is always consistent and am always happy to dine here real quick. Never had a problem...

The flower on the  table is always a nice touch, the place is extremely clean, and everything is just well organized. Every other fast food place should copy this system.

This is how I received my breakfast burrito this morning. Very disappointed! I did curbside, got my order drove off immediately to make it work on time. Arrived at work to see this when I unwrapped my burrito. I've never received quality this bad at a Chick-fil-A. I think I will avoid this location from now on.

We had a gentleman named Robert and a female employee a plus sized associate with short hair with red highlights deny us a manager and confront us. Didn’t give us professional service. I felt I was treated like a “homeless person” because of my unique style. When asked “for here or to go” the tone is something I heard before but it’s not okay I will keep reporting it. And sooner or later these people have to realize they’re actions are not okay.

I order curbside, like the location, and wish they had more space. Their service is impeccable.

I love it when they hand over the goods, I say thank you, and the Chick-fil-A staff member's go-to response is "my pleasure."❤

I have always been a fan of the Yekta market. While I ate at the restaurant on occasion, I always found it super overpriced. Now that they closed the dining room and turned it into a full supermarket with kitchen counter - it's much better.

They now offer bowls for a more casual dining option which I love. I always go for the lamb or chicken kubideh with all the eggplant purees, shirazi salad, and sautéed vegetables instead of rice. I also love all their stews, especially the ghorma sabzi - reminds me of my grandma's! The tahdig is super thick and the portions are so generous!

The market is great and has everything you would need, from great cheeses to pantry items, frozen items, fresh produce, breads and cookies. They also have prepared foods for sale which is also super convenient.

Everything here is higher priced, but worth it.

Service is good.

They make great kabobs. The combination of meat, rice, salad, grilled tomato, bread, and seasoning will leave you feeling full and satisfied. I have eaten here about five times so far and have not been disappointed.
Tasty, easy dinner option, either meat or vegan options for bowls and for other prepped foods. Loved "Ash" soup (a qt was $8, at cheese display area). We're sold on this rather than fast food!

I’ve been eating Yekta for years, and although I miss the sit down restaurant, the food is just as wonderful as takeout as it was dining in. They have the friendliest staff, and they also catered my wedding a few years ago. All the guests loved it and to this day, they tell me how they order from here because of the great experience from the wedding.
Yekta Kabob counter is wonderful. I order online and the food is always ready when I arrive.  I have ordered for lunch and dinner for ourselves and when we have guests.

I have been enjoying the Unlimited Sip Club for many months. It is easy and convenient to place a drink order on mobile in advance. The drink would be ready for pickup within about ten minutes. The Mango Yuzu Citrus Lemonade Charged with Caffeine was great since it was introduced last year. I like no ice in it over winter months.

What I love about this place is the service, it is very good and fast. The staff is competent and do there work. I enkoyed watching some older staff working and helping out, keeping the place clean, though I feel they were managers or owners (Which is great they work the floor with staff if am right).

Broccoli and Cheddar: I always order the exact some thing every time I come here. The best part is that I got a complete fresh batch of it! Straight out the bag! I wish I can just buy that bag and go home. Always good and consistant. It tastes exactly like its name, perfect~

Nice place to come for some gru. and maybe lounge around and chat with friends or have meetings.

Horrible service from the manager!

I ordered a Chicken Baja bowl w/o feta cheese and no beans. I don’t do cheese or dairy.  Called to speak with the manager, Katie said next time ask for a lactose menu. REALLY?? Which part of I don’t do cheese or diary is confusing???!!!
Management needs to train Katie to listen and apologize to the customer when a customer calls to tell you about the purchased item and is unhappy with it.

quickly served and had a friendly staff! I had the Mac and cheese and it was very well seasoned and the portion was a great size. The baguette was fresh as well! The prices are a little high though so expect to pay $10 or more for a meal.

The more I visit, the lesser consistency of the food and more customers for some stupid reason.

Less toppings, less dressing, less everything. It becomes more and more bland. Meanwhile the one in Rockville Town Square had better consistency and better quality, but not enough customers.

Not so fresh tasting Thai, our order tasted like it was prepped yesterday and simply reheated today. Portions were oddly small and unevenly flavored.

Our Beef Mussaman was the best of the three dishes and sadly this entree had the smallest broth portion. Flavoring was controlled without anything being overpowering. The beef was indeed soft and the two potato chunks were just right.

Our green curry was way too spicy (we asked for a two out of five) and we lost every other flavor of the dish after the first bite.

The Tom Ke Hed soup had way too much fish sauce in the broth and the vegetables tasted like they were a day or two short of their expiration date. Again, the portion was very small.

Thankfully our dinner arrived warm so we got a fair expectation of what the meal should taste like.
This is really good. If you go on a weeknight there's no wait. We got the pad Thai and panang curry which was really good. The curry was really coconut heavy. Highly recommend

The food is consistently delicious. We go for the Pad Thai but have liked Ginger Perfect, and Siamese Beef. Guys, this place delivers always. My family and I have been coming here for years. Consistently delicious. What can I say!

It's not a restaurant. It's a diner. Table surfaces are sticky. Boxes are dumped in the back of the dining hall. Price/quality is high. You either decrease prices or increase quality. The soup was way sour, yet, nothing says about it on the menu. Thai iced coffee and some noodles were good. If I were an owner I would entirely renovate this business and change the chef.
Soup was tasty and fresh. No coconut juice in stock. Coconut custard pie rubbery. Calamari appetizer inedible and sent back. Shrimp cakes were likely frozen. Would not return. Very disappointed.

Amazing restaurant with northern dim sum and Chinese fare. Love their spicy beef noodle soup. Make sure to get with the wide noodles! Also love the dumplings, scallion pancake, Peking beef roll, sliced pork ears and beef tripe with hot red sauce. Everything is so flavorful and fresh, and the staff is so nice and welcoming! Can’t wait to come back again and try more of the menu!

As a Taiwanese person I’ve been craving this kind of food, and I was not disappointed! The broth in the 牛肉麵 is superb and the thin noodles cooked perfectly. My only complaint is that the 鍋貼 皮 is a little too thick and not crispy enough. I will definitely return, and I wish this place was closer to where I lived!

Amazing service and authentic food. We loved the spicy wontons in chili sauce and Dan Dan noodles. Noodles themselves are worth a return trip. We also tried several other dishes! For 2 of us we ordered 5 dishes and it was perfect. We came around 7:45pm and the food was still hot and fresh. Thank you so much for an amazing meal and we will definitely come back!

My go to place for beef noodle soup. Broth is relatively spicy and flavorful. You can choose either flat or thin noodles. I personally like thin noodle better. Beef chunks are really tender and perfectly complement the soup. I also ordered pan fried pork dumplings and dan dan noodle. Both dishes were really good too. Service was just okay. Definitely has room for improvements. Parking spaces can be limited depends on what time you get there. They used to only accept cash, but I believe they now use venom for the payment. I highly recommend this place if you are craving spicy beef noodle soup.

While the hand made noodles are super chewy and have excellent texture and taste (make sure you order wide noodles and not the thin ones), the side dishes that we ordered were lacking. The pan fried dumplings were on the greasy side and stuck together and the filling was under seasoned. The Peking beef wrap was really disappointing. In other restaurants, I’ve had it with cucumber and scallion and scallion pancake. Here, it was filled with shredded carrot and cilantro (and the requisite beef) but just doesn’t hold a candle to beef wraps I’ve had in other Taiwanese restaurants. That said, for the area (DMV) This place is a good place to go to. I also find it overpriced for what you get but I’m spoiled as I do come from Vancouver Canada where they have the best Asian food ever. I do love however that they take venmo! Yay!
Great service and quality drinks. Small location but huge windows for people watching. Located in the far corner of the shopping center

I ordered 2 drinks on the mobile app & waited to go in at my designated time. 1 drink was ready. The barista did not know how to make a London Fog Latte, she offered to put cold lemonade in it! Then, 20 mins later she poured cold heavy cream into the cup & handed to me. It took 5 calls & when they answered they would not credit me back for the wrong drink bc they were too busy. Worst experience at SBX ever! Worst store!!!
Excellent service and helpful for deaf persons!
Best Starbucks I have been too in awhile. Baristas were super fast and friendly, inclusive atmosphere, great music. Definitely left with a smile on my face.
Perfectly ok Starbucks. A bit cramped. Baristas amiable.

Service was impeccable and Food was all delicious - really enjoyed our visit here for lunch as always.

Hummus was great and the lamb perfectly cooked.

Garlic dip is the best too!

We’ll be back!

What a terrific experience.  Maroun the area manager was amazing.  He treated us like family.  He explained everything on the menu and gave us delicious suggestions. He checked on us all the time and made sure our visit was perfect  We feel very blessed to have met Maroun.  The labneh and hummus are my favorite but honestly all the food was outstanding.  The chicken shawarma was so flavorful.  I recommend getting a sampler to try a variety of things.  Please do not hesitate to try this place. Run don't walk.... this place is top notch in our book. Thank you 🙏 😊 💓
Excellent lamb shawarma and extremely fast and friendly service. Very reasonably priced for the area. Highly recommended.

I was recently in town visiting family and came across this gem! The food was very authentic to traditional Lebanese food and everything was truly delicious and enjoyable. I highly recommend the appetizer combination and the chicken shawarma. They even had ice cold Almaza beer which is extremely hard to find in the states. Service was wonderful and the owner was very friendly.
Everything is fabulous there.  I have just discovered the Chicken Shawarma Salad so that is my new obsession.  Great food and service too. Can't ask for anything more!

My husband & I just went here for the all
you can eat lunch.
We got sat immediately- the staff was so kind and responsive… the whole experience was very seamless.
And the food was AMAZING! Really everything I had was delicious and took no longer than 5 minutes to be prepared.
(I am also pregnant so I consider myself to be an extremely picky eater right now. So this is quite literally the best review I have ever given any restaurant.)
10/10 worth it!!!

Nice lunch & dinner all you can eat with some restrictions on quantity but still reasonable. I had a nice salad, miso soup, Korean bulgogi, kimchi, cucumber salad and a nice tuna roll with some nice pieces of salmon, tuna & mackerel sushi. It was prepared nicely snd I really enjoyed myself. The bulgogi portion was a bit small but tasty nevertheless.

TLDR: Endless Sushi and Japanese/Korean eats at a reasonable price! Both maki and nigiri were delicious.

Vibe: 3/5. Located in a small strip mall off Congressional, parking at Hinode can sometimes be tough. The strip mall has several popular businesses inside, so parking during peak times can be scarce. On several occasions we have had to street park on nearby side streets and walk to the restaurant. The inside of Hinode is your pretty basic sushi restaurant. Dozens of 4 tops and a large wooden sushi bar occupy the bulk of the main dining area. They have several rooms full of tables, so getting a table is usually quite easy, even for larger groups. The decor is a bit antiquated , but it is clean and they do have 3 very nicely maintained fish tanks at the front that are a joy to watch while you dine.

Service: 5/5. The staff have always been very nice and accommodating at Hinode. On our most recent visit for weekend lunch, service lived up to that expectation. We were seated immediately and given the all you can eat menus with our order taken promptly. Both the kitchen and the sushi chefs were quick in getting the food out and our waiter was on top of the beverage refills. Couldn't ask for a better experience .

Food: 4/5. Before the pandemic, Hinode used to be a predominantly buffet style restaurant, offering sushi and Japanese/Korean food on the bar for you to take at your leisure. Post pandemic, they have transitioned to an all you can order style of dining, which in my opinion produces a better overall experience. The sushi comes out fresher and you are always guaranteed to get what you want. On my most recent lunch, the sushi was well prepared and generous in fish portion size. The hot foods were also exceptional, offering a delicious alternative to prevent sushi palate fatigue. The portion sizes for each sushi order are also nicely thought out (1 nigiri and 4 pieces per roll) so diners won't get full off of a single roll or 2. Overall, for the price of $23-30 depending if you down for lunch or dinner, Hinode is a great choice for sushioholics

I've been looking for an AYCE sushi place ever since I moved here and I still haven't found one that does it for me. (This review is only for the AYCE, no idea what their a la carte is like)

I came by myself on a Thursday around 6pm, not too much people, but people started coming in as I was finishing up.

For ~$30/person, not bad price-wise. If you bump it up to $35/person, you can order sashimi too, but I wasn't feeling that. In total, I got about 10 pieces of nigiri, 6 rolls, and 2 skewers of chicken.

First off, I can understand AYCE establishments putting small amounts of fish with large amounts of rice, that's understandable, but at least make the rice taste good. It was colder than room temperature (you don't want sushi rice to be warm though) and kind of dry tasting. The fish itself was alright.

The chicken skewers were honestly really bad. The chicken had very little flavor and it was really hard to chew, almost like it had been overcooked.

For the money, you can definitely get a lot of food, but it's not that enjoyable.

Five stars ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
What a great deal, all you can eat Shushi, seven days a week!  A good variety; sushi, nigiri, sashimi, miso soup, salad, Korean BBQ, Bulgogi, terryaki chicken...  I'm not a sushi expert.  I enjoyed my meal and so did the two others with me.   The sushi rolls were so filling.  I recommend ordering the nigiri, and a limited amount of sushi rolls.  For those of you who don't eat much just order á la carte.  A California roll without caviar is only $5.75.  pair that with miso soup and green tea and you have a meal for about $11.  A bargain!  Very large seating area and an area in the back you may reserve for large parties.  Take out service is popular.  Decent parking, one handicap parking space for the entire row of businesses, so be prepared to wait a little bit for a good parking space if you need to park near the entrance.  Definitely worth checking out.  Enjoy!
Great environment/ service. I'd give 4 1/5 stars I wasn't a fan of the chicken francaice too much lemon to it comparing for other same dish I've had before.

I have been a customer for over 15 years. Bottom line…the best value and authentic Italian cuisine in town. A ten inch pepperoni pizza only $10.00…best deal in town. The lasagna and garlic bread is a must order. Their service is top notch as well. Kudos to them!

Had Mama Lucia of Rockville Pike cater my daughter’s Bat Mitzvah and could it not have been more perfect.  Bradley, the manager is amazing and made the process so easy.  Food was delicious and fresh! Highly recommend them.  They also had servers and bartenders they can include with the catering and they were also very professional and extremely helpful.

This had horrible service.  My daughter ordered from the appetizer menu at 1pm. It didn't come until after 1:45. None of our meals came at the same time. Everything was staggered. Her white pizza was Luke warm and you can tell it was sitting  not being served. The antipasto salad was heavy on a bottled dressing  . My husband and son both had the same food and it still was 10 to 15 minutes apart.  I would pass on this very non Italian bottled processed food . Growing up in an Italian family I can tell you this was straight out of a jar and bottle.

Original post 9/21/2022: I am European and this review might be harsh but I have to tell you the truth. It's not Italian food. Absolutely not. It's definitely very fresh ingredients but unfortunately got nothing to do with Italian cuisine. A shame that these fresh ingredients do not become an original italian dish. That's not a lasagna. That's meat with cream cheese divided by pasta plates. They just drizzle the tomato sauce on top of the lasagna so it is literally bathing in the tomato sauce. Mushroom ravioli were good. Not delicious but good. As long you do not expect to have Italian cuisine served, this place is quite ok. Pizzas were looking good. We will definitely try one of those next time.

Wow. Had to change my rating from 3 to 1 star since the chef seems not to be open for critic.
